        "kind": "pull_request",
        "title": "[codex] Coalesce daily generation in Durable Object",
        "body": "## Summary\n\n- make the per-host Durable Object the sole owner of daily AI generation\n- coalesce concurrent `/daily` and `/stream` misses behind one in-flight promise\n- keep live streams `no-store` until a complete canonical record is stored\n- treat malformed, truncated, timed-out, or disconnected upstream streams as failures and persist deterministic fallback text\n- keep Durable Object storage bounded to one record per version, with migration of the current legacy date key\n- update regression tests, documentation, and the changelog; preserve contributor credit\n\n## Why\n\nCloudflare edge cache entries are data-center local, so they cannot enforce the project's one-generation-per-host-per-UTC-day invariant. The Durable Object now owns that invariant. A first `/stream` request can still stream live output, while concurrent requests wait on the same generation and receive only the stored complete record.\n\nThe repair also closes operational failure modes in the original patch: caching a stream clone before completion, ending the timeout after response headers, accepting SSE without `[DONE]`, caching a Worker-local fallback that could diverge from Durable Object state, and unbounded date-key storage growth.\n\n## Validation\n\n- `pnpm check` — typecheck, lint, format, and 15 tests\n- `pnpm dlx wrangler@4 deploy --dry-run`\n- real local Wrangler Durable Object runtime with an OpenAI-compatible mock:\n  - five concurrent cold requests produced exactly one upstream call\n  - live `/stream` and following `/` produced byte-identical canonical output\n  - forced midstream disconnect returned an interruption marker to that client, stored a deterministic fallback, and never cached partial output\n- two clean `$autoreview` passes: dirty maintainer repair and exact committed branch diff\n- Public Model Identifier Gate: PASS — `grok-4-1-fast-reasoning` is an official xAI alias; xAI documents its redirect behavior in the [May 15 retirement notice](https://docs.x.ai/developers/migration/may-15-retirement)\n\n## Merge gate\n\nAuthenticated provider proof remains pending. The available scoped secret context does not expose an xAI credential; no production deployment or secret mutation was attempted. Merge after that exact live proof or an explicit item-specific proof waiver.\n",
